  "exercisePushS1WallPushupName": "Wall Push-up",
  "exercisePushS1WallPushupDesc": "Stand a step away from the wall and press your palms at chest height. Bend your arms until your chest touches the wall, then push back.",
  "exercisePushS1WallPushupTip": "Keep your body straight — don't arch your lower back.",
  "exercisePushS2KneePushupName": "Knee Push-up",
  "exercisePushS2KneePushupDesc": "Push-up position with knees on the floor. Keep a straight line from knees to head. Lower your chest to the floor, then press up.",
  "exercisePushS2KneePushupTip": "Don't drop your hips — keep a straight line from knees to shoulders.",
  "exercisePushS3FullPushupName": "Full Push-up",
  "exercisePushS3FullPushupDesc": "Classic push-up position. Body forms a straight line from heels to head. Chest touches or comes within 2–3 cm of the floor.",
  "exercisePushS3FullPushupTip": "Brace your core and glutes to keep your hips from sagging.",
  "exercisePushS4DiamondPushupName": "Diamond Push-up",
  "exercisePushS4DiamondPushupDesc": "Hands under your chest with thumbs and index fingers forming a diamond. Targets the triceps. Keep elbows tucked on the way down.",
  "exercisePushS4DiamondPushupTip": "Don't flare your elbows — let them glide along your body.",
  "exercisePushS5WidePushupName": "Wide Push-up",
  "exercisePushS5WidePushupDesc": "Hands placed significantly wider than shoulder-width. Lower slowly while keeping your body in a straight line. Both chest and triceps work through a wide range of motion.",
  "exercisePushS5WidePushupTip": "The wider your hands, the more the chest is targeted and the less the triceps.",
  "exercisePushS6ArcherPushupName": "Archer Push-up",
  "exercisePushS6ArcherPushupDesc": "Wide hand placement. Lower toward one arm while keeping the other arm straight. Alternate each side.",
  "exercisePushS6ArcherPushupTip": "Working arm goes full range; straight arm stays on the floor for support.",
  "exercisePushS7HandstandPushupName": "Handstand Push-up",
  "exercisePushS7HandstandPushupDesc": "Handstand against the wall (back to wall). Slowly lower your head toward the floor, then press your body back up.",
  "exercisePushS7HandstandPushupTip": "Spread your fingers wide for stability. Look between your hands.",
  "exerciseCoreS1CrunchesName": "Crunches",
  "exerciseCoreS1CrunchesDesc": "Lie on your back with knees bent. Hands behind your head or crossed on your chest. Lift your shoulder blades off the floor by contracting your abs.",
  "exerciseCoreS1CrunchesTip": "Don't pull your neck with your hands — pull your chest toward the ceiling.",
  "exerciseCoreS2PlankName": "Plank",
  "exerciseCoreS2PlankDesc": "Forearm push-up position. Body forms a straight line from heels to head. Don't raise your hips or arch your lower back.",
  "exerciseCoreS2PlankTip": "Brace your core and glutes. Breathe steadily — don't hold your breath.",
  "exerciseCoreS3LyingLegRaiseName": "Lying Leg Raise",
  "exerciseCoreS3LyingLegRaiseDesc": "Lie on your back with hands under your glutes. Raise straight legs to vertical, then lower them slowly without touching the floor.",
  "exerciseCoreS3LyingLegRaiseTip": "Keep your lower back pressed to the floor throughout the movement.",
  "exerciseCoreS4HangingLegRaiseName": "Hanging Leg Raise",
  "exerciseCoreS4HangingLegRaiseDesc": "Hang from a bar. Raise straight legs to parallel with the floor or higher. Control the descent.",
  "exerciseCoreS4HangingLegRaiseTip": "Don't swing — the movement comes from your abs only.",
  "exerciseCoreS4FlutterKicksName": "Flutter Kicks",
  "exerciseCoreS4FlutterKicksDesc": "Lie on your back, hands under your glutes. Lift both legs 15–20 cm off the floor. Alternate raising and lowering each leg in small quick movements. One rep = one cycle (right up + left up).",
  "exerciseCoreS4FlutterKicksTip": "Keep your lower back pressed to the floor. Legs don't touch the floor between reps.",
  "exerciseCoreS5LSitName": "L-sit",
  "exerciseCoreS5LSitDesc": "Support on parallel bars or the floor. Legs straight and parallel to the floor. Hold the position as long as possible.",
  "exerciseCoreS5LSitTip": "Point toes toward you; pull shoulders down and back.",
  "exerciseCoreS6DragonFlagName": "Dragon Flag",
  "exerciseCoreS6DragonFlagDesc": "Lie on a bench and grip a support behind your head. Lift your body into a straight line on your shoulder blades, then lower slowly.",
  "exerciseCoreS6DragonFlagTip": "Start with the negative phase (lowering only) — it's easier.",
  "exerciseWarmupArmRotationsName": "Arm Circles",
  "exerciseWarmupArmRotationsDesc": "Standing, make large circular movements with your arms forward and backward. Warms up the shoulder girdle before push-ups.",
  "exerciseWarmupJumpingJacksName": "Jumping Jacks",
  "exerciseWarmupJumpingJacksDesc": "Classic jumping jacks. Raises your heart rate and warms up your whole body in 30–60 seconds.",
  "exerciseCooldownShoulderStretchName": "Shoulder & Chest Stretch",
  "exerciseCooldownShoulderStretchDesc": "Clasp your hands behind your back and pull your shoulders back and down. Hold for 30 seconds.",
  "exerciseCooldownCatCowName": "Cat-Cow",
  "exerciseCooldownCatCowDesc": "On all fours: inhale and arch your back down (cow), exhale and round it up (cat). Releases tension in the lower back and abs.",
  "exercisePullS1AustralianName": "Australian Pull-up",
  "exercisePullS1AustralianDesc": "Lie under a bar with a slightly wider than shoulder-width grip. Pull your chest to the bar, keeping your body in a straight line. Control the descent.",
  "exercisePullS1AustralianTip": "The lower the bar, the harder the exercise.",
  "exercisePullS2NegativeName": "Negative Pull-up",
  "exercisePullS2NegativeDesc": "Jump up with your chin above the bar. Slowly lower yourself over 3–5 seconds until your arms are fully extended.",
  "exercisePullS2NegativeTip": "The slower you lower — the better. Aim for 5 seconds down.",
  "exercisePullS3PullupName": "Pull-up",
  "exercisePullS3PullupDesc": "Shoulder-width or slightly wider grip. Pull your chest to the bar until your chin is above it. Fully extend your arms at the bottom.",
  "exercisePullS3PullupTip": "Squeeze your shoulder blades — you're pulling with your back, not your arms.",
  "exercisePullS4CloseGripName": "Close-Grip Pull-up",
  "exercisePullS4CloseGripDesc": "Grip narrower than shoulder-width, palms facing you or away. Targets the biceps and lower lats. Pull your chest to the bar.",
  "exercisePullS4CloseGripTip": "Keep elbows tucked in for maximum bicep engagement.",
  "exercisePullS5ArcherName": "Archer Pull-up",
  "exercisePullS5ArcherDesc": "Wide grip. Pull your body toward one arm while keeping the other arm straight. Alternate each side.",
  "exercisePullS5ArcherTip": "Straight arm is for support; working arm goes full range.",
  "exercisePullS6OneArmName": "One-Arm Pull-up",
  "exercisePullS6OneArmDesc": "One hand on the bar, the other on your wrist or free. Full range of motion with the working arm.",
  "exercisePullS6OneArmTip": "Keep your core tight — don't swing.",
  "exerciseWarmupDeadHangName": "Dead Hang",
  "exerciseWarmupDeadHangDesc": "Hang from the bar with an overhand grip, arms fully extended. Relax your shoulders and hold the hang.",
  "exerciseCooldownLatStretchName": "Lat Stretch",
  "exerciseCooldownLatStretchDesc": "Stand sideways to a wall, raise one arm and press against it. Lean into the stretch to feel it along your side.",
  "exerciseLegsS1SquatName": "Squat",
  "exerciseLegsS1SquatDesc": "Feet shoulder-width apart, toes slightly turned out. Squat until thighs are parallel to the floor, knees over toes. Extend fully at the top.",
  "exerciseLegsS1SquatTip": "Keep heels on the floor and chest upright.",
  "exerciseLegsS2LungeName": "Lunge",
  "exerciseLegsS2LungeDesc": "Step forward and lower your back knee toward the floor without touching it. Both knees at 90°. Push off with the front foot to return.",
  "exerciseLegsS2LungeTip": "Keep your front knee behind your toes.",
  "exerciseLegsS3BulgarianName": "Bulgarian Split Squat",
  "exerciseLegsS3BulgarianDesc": "Rear foot elevated on a chair or couch. Lower your front leg until your thigh is parallel to the floor. Keep your torso upright.",
  "exerciseLegsS3BulgarianTip": "The further your front foot, the more glute activation.",
  "exerciseLegsS4AssistedPistolName": "Assisted Pistol Squat",
  "exerciseLegsS4AssistedPistolDesc": "Hold a door frame or pole for support. Squat on one leg while keeping the other straight in front of you. Use the support to reduce load.",
  "exerciseLegsS4AssistedPistolTip": "Gradually reduce hand assistance as you get stronger.",
  "exerciseLegsS5PistolName": "Pistol Squat",
  "exerciseLegsS5PistolDesc": "Single-leg squat without support. Other leg straight in front. Full range of motion to the floor and back up.",
  "exerciseLegsS5PistolTip": "Arms forward as a counterweight — it helps with balance.",
  "exerciseWarmupLegSwingsName": "Leg Swings",
  "exerciseWarmupLegSwingsDesc": "Standing by a wall, swing one leg forward and back, then side to side. Warms up the hip joint.",
  "exerciseCooldownQuadStretchName": "Quad Stretch",
  "exerciseCooldownQuadStretchDesc": "Stand on one leg, bend the other back and hold your foot with your hand. Feel the stretch along the front of your thigh.",
  "exerciseWarmupHipCirclesName": "Hip Circles",
  "exerciseWarmupHipCirclesDesc": "Stand with feet shoulder-width apart. Make slow circular movements with your hips clockwise then counter-clockwise. Warms up the hip joints.",
  "exerciseCooldownHipFlexorName": "Hip Flexor Stretch",
  "exerciseCooldownHipFlexorDesc": "Step into a lunge and lower your back knee to the floor. Press your hips forward and down to feel the stretch in your hip. Hold each side.",
  "exerciseBalS1OneLegStandName": "One-Leg Stand",
  "exerciseBalS1OneLegStandDesc": "Stand on one leg, keep the other slightly bent and off the ground. Arms can be out for balance.",
  "exerciseBalS1OneLegStandTip": "Fix your gaze on a point — it greatly improves balance.",
  "exerciseBalS2OneArmPlankName": "One-Arm Plank",
  "exerciseBalS2OneArmPlankDesc": "Classic straight-arm plank. Lift one hand off the floor and hold the position, body parallel to the floor.",
  "exerciseBalS2OneArmPlankTip": "Keep your hips parallel to the floor — don't rotate your torso.",
  "exerciseBalS3CrowPrepName": "Crow Pose Prep",
  "exerciseBalS3CrowPrepDesc": "Squat with knees on your triceps. Shift weight onto your hands, gently lifting your feet. Hold the balance.",
  "exerciseBalS3CrowPrepTip": "Look forward-down, not straight down — or you'll tip over.",
  "exerciseBalS4CrowPoseName": "Crow Pose (Kakasana)",
  "exerciseBalS4CrowPoseDesc": "Both knees on your triceps, full balance on your hands. Arms slightly bent, fingers spread wide.",
  "exerciseBalS4CrowPoseTip": "Round your back — it engages your core and provides balance.",
  "exerciseBalS5WallHsName": "Wall Handstand",
  "exerciseBalS5WallHsDesc": "Kick up into a handstand with your back to the wall. Heels touch the wall for support. Hold the position, body in a straight line.",
  "exerciseBalS5WallHsTip": "Spread fingers wide and press through the pads — that's your balance control.",
  "exerciseBalS6FreeHsName": "Free Handstand",
  "exerciseBalS6FreeHsDesc": "Handstand without wall support. Control balance with small finger and wrist movements.",
  "exerciseBalS6FreeHsTip": "Look at the floor 30–40 cm in front of your hands, not between them.",
  "exerciseWarmupWristCirclesName": "Wrist Circles",
  "exerciseWarmupWristCirclesDesc": "Rotate your wrists clockwise and counter-clockwise. Prepares your joints for weight-bearing on your hands.",
  "exerciseCooldownDownwardDogName": "Downward Dog",
  "exerciseCooldownDownwardDogDesc": "From all fours, straighten arms and legs and lift your hips up. Body forms an inverted V. Stretches wrists, shoulders, and legs.",
  "exerciseCooldownWristStretchName": "Wrist Stretch",
  "exerciseCooldownWristStretchDesc": "Extend one arm forward, palm up. Use your other hand to gently pull the fingers down. Hold for 30 seconds per side.",
